Here's the proper approach using MAUI's app lifecycle events and `Preferences`:

**In your `App.xaml.cs`**, hook into lifecycle events:

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    public App()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        MainPage = new NavigationPage(new NotePage());
    }

    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
    {
        var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);

        window.Deactivated += (s, e) =>
            WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new AppLifecycleMessage(false));

        window.Activated += (s, e) =>
            WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new AppLifecycleMessage(true));

        return window;
    }
}

// Simple message class
public class AppLifecycleMessage(bool isActive)
{
    public bool IsActive { get; } = isActive;
}
```

**In your `NotePage` (or its ViewModel)**:

```csharp
public partial class NotePage : ContentPage
{
    private readonly Editor _editor;
    private const string DraftKey = "note_draft";

    public NotePage()
    {
        _editor = new Editor { Placeholder = "Start typing..." };
        Content = _editor;

        // Restore draft on creation
        _editor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);

        // Listen for lifecycle changes
        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Register<AppLifecycleMessage>(this, (r, m) =>
        {
            if (!m.IsActive)
                SaveDraft();
            // No restore needed on resume — text is already in the editor
        });
    }

    private void SaveDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Set(DraftKey, _editor.Text ?? string.Empty);
    }

    // Also save when navigating away
    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        SaveDraft();
    }
}
```

> Requires the `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` NuGet for `WeakReferenceMessenger`.  
> Install: `dotnet add package CommunityToolkit.Mvvm`

**Key points:**

- **`Window.Deactivated`** fires when the app goes to background — save here.
- **`Preferences`** is a simple key-value store that persists across sessions.
- **`WeakReferenceMessenger`** decouples lifecycle events from page logic and avoids memory leaks.
- For larger drafts, swap `Preferences` for `File.WriteAllTextAsync` to a path from `FileSystem.AppDataDirectory`.
